{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}} {{Infobox Bibliographic Database |title = International Philosophical Bibliography |producer = [[Université catholique de Louvain|UCLouvain]] |history = 1934–present |languages = English, French |providers = [[Peeters Publishers]] |cost = Subscription |disciplines = Philosophy |depth = Index and keywords |formats = |temporal = |geospatial = Worldwide |number = > 1 million |update = Quarterly | p_title = | p_dates = |web = http://pob.peeters-leuven.be/content.php |titles = }} The '''International Philosophical Bibliography''' ('''IPB'''), also known in French as ''Répertoire bibliographique de la philosophie'' (RBP), is a [[bibliographic database]] covering publications on the history of philosophy and [[continental philosophy]].<ref name="POB">{{Cite web|url=http://pob.peeters-leuven.be/content.php|title=International Philosophical Bibliography|publisher=Peeters Online Bibliographies|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>
The database comprises records of publications in over 30 languages. Annually, about 12,000 records are added.<ref name="POB" /> The indexes include, among other elements, over 84,000 names of authors, editors, translators, reviewers, and collaborators, as well as more than 3,000 commentaries on philosophical works, making it the world's most complete index in Philosophy.<ref name="HIW">{{Cite web|url=https://hiw.kuleuven.be/en/about-us/facts-and-figures|title=KU Leuven Institute of Philosophy|publisher=[[KU Leuven]]|language=en|accessdate=5 April 2020|quote=The world's most complete index in Philosophy: the International Philosophical Bibliography}}</ref>
Since 1934, the IPB has been developed by the [[Higher Institute of Philosophy]] at the [[Université catholique de Louvain|University of Louvain]] (UCLouvain), first in [[Leuven]] and since 1978 in [[Louvain-la-Neuve]].<ref name="UCLouvain">{{Cite web|url=https://uclouvain.be/fr/instituts-recherche/isp/ipb.html|title= Répertoire bibliographique de la philosophie|publisher=[[UCLouvain]]|language=fr|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> The online version was launched by [[Peeters Publishers]] in 1997 and continues to be updated quarterly.
